items.title: UStrive security lapse exposed personal data of its users, including children
items.summary: The online mentoring site UStrive exposed email addresses, phone numbers, and other non-public information to other logged-in users. The nonprofit told TechCrunch that the issue is now fixed, but wouldn't commit to alerting affected individuals.

items.title: Retail startup Another raises a $2.5M seed to help sell excess inventory

items.summary: The federal safety agency has hit SpaceX with a $115,850 fine after finding seven "serious" violations during its investigation.

items.title: Netflix is rolling out a live voting feature
items.summary: Netflix said that the feature will work globally, and the platform will tally votes in real time. Viewers will have a limited time to vote, and once that time has lapsed, additional votes won't count. That means if you're watching the show later, you can't participate in the voting.

items.title: Netflix revises offer to pay all cash for Warner Bros. to fend off Paramount
items.summary: However, the streaming giant is still offering the same $27.75 the companies had agreed on for WBD's movie studio and streaming assets, and the deal continues to value the company at $82.7 billion.

items.summary: TechCrunch Disrupt Battlefield 2023 winner BioticsAI announced on Monday that it has received FDA clearance for its AI software that helps detect fetal abnormalities in ultrasound images.
